<Layouts.app flash={@flash}>
  <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-12 mt-5 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <.custom_nav active="chelekom-docs-avatar" />
    <div class="lg:col-span-10">
      <.custom_info
        title="Avatar"
        description="Interactive avatars and avatar groups for Phoenix and Phoenix LiveView, displaying profile images, initials, or fallback icons, with options to group avatars for a cohesive display."
        mix="mix mishka.ui.gen.component avatar"
        github="https://github.com/mishka-group/mishka_chelekom/blob/master/priv/components/avatar.eex"
        tags={["Component", "Stateless"]}
      />
      <.custom_tab id="chelekom-avatar-tab">
        <:documentation_panel>
          <.heading2 class="mb-5" id="overview">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#overview"}>
              Overview of the Phoenix and LiveView Avatar Component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <strong>
              Mishka Chelekom Avatar
            </strong>
            component allows you to display user profile images, initials, or a fallback icon when no image is available. It's a versatile component that adapts to various user data inputs, ensuring that each profile is represented visually in a consistent and elegant manner. For group displays, the
            <strong>Avatar Group</strong>
            component arranges multiple avatars in a compact, visually appealing layout, making it perfect for team views or social interactions within your application. This module integrates seamlessly with
            <strong>Phoenix</strong>
            and <strong>Phoenix LiveView</strong>.
          </.cp>
          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="flex gap-3 items-center text-sm">
            <.avatar id="avatar3" color="danger" rounded="full">
              SB
            </.avatar>
            <.avatar
              id="avatar2"
              border="extra_small"
              class="border-[#E5E7EB]"
              src={~p"/images/avatar2.jpg"}
            />
            <.avatar color="dawn" id="avatar1">
              <:icon name="hero-star" />
            </.avatar>

            <.avatar_group id="ex-1" space="extra_small">
              <.avatar id="avatar70090" src={~p"/images/avatar1.png"} size="small" rounded="full" />
              <.avatar id="avatar70091" src={~p"/images/avatar2.jpg"} size="small" rounded="full" />
              <.avatar id="avatar70092" src={~p"/images/avatar4.jpg"} size="small" rounded="full" />
              <.avatar
                id="avatar70093"
                size="small"
                color="misc"
                class="shadow-sm"
                rounded="full"
                border="extra_small"
              >
                +20
              </.avatar>
            </.avatar_group>
            <.badge
              size="small"
              variant="bordered"
              color="silver"
              rounded="full"
              content_class="flex flex-nowrap items-center gap-2 flex-1"
            >
              <.avatar_group id="ex-421" space="small">
                <.avatar
                  id="avatar70234"
                  src={~p"/images/avatar1.png"}
                  size="extra_small"
                  rounded="full"
                />
                <.avatar
                  id="avatar70ddas"
                  src={~p"/images/avatar2.jpg"}
                  size="extra_small"
                  rounded="full"
                />
                <.avatar
                  id="avatar7fgp"
                  src={~p"/images/avatar3.jpg"}
                  size="extra_small"
                  rounded="full"
                />
              </.avatar_group>
              <span class="text-[15px] font-semibold">
                25 people Signed up
              </span>
            </.badge>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.cp>
            This
            <strong>
              <.link
                title="Phoenix LiveView component"
                class="transition-colors hover:text-[#448D96]"
                navigate={~p"/chelekom"}
              >
                Phoenix LiveView component
              </.link>
            </strong>
            offers a variety of options to customize your user avatars. You can stack avatars on top of each other as a group, add borders for emphasis, include status indicators, and much more. These features make the avatar component highly flexible, allowing it to fit seamlessly into any design while enhancing the visual representation of user profiles.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_block position="left" color="success" class="my-8" border="medium">
            <.cp>
              By using the class prop, you can apply custom classes or Tailwind CSS classes to customize the appearance and behavior of the components, allowing for flexible design changes.
            </.cp>
          </.custom_block>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="avatar-colors">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#avatar-colors"}>
              Avatar colors
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The
            <.custom_inline_code>color</.custom_inline_code>
            attribute in the avatar component defines the theme and appearance of the divider by offering a wide range of color options. You can choose from predefined color values such as <.custom_inline_code>base</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>natural</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>white</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>dark</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>primary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>secondary</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>success</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>warning</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>danger</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>info</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>misc</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>dawn</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>silver</.custom_inline_code>. The default color is set to <.custom_inline_code>silver</.custom_inline_code>, but you can easily customize the color theme to match the design and style of your application.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_1}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar color="base" id="avatar13234">
                <:icon name="hero-star" />
              </.avatar>

              <.avatar color="natural" id="avatar1">
                <:icon name="hero-star" />
              </.avatar>

              <.avatar
                id="avatar24234"
                border="extra_small"
                color="dawn"
                src={~p"/images/avatar2.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar id="avatar3">
                SB
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar20" border="extra_small" color="dawn">
                MD
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar21" color="misc">
                Fh
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar22" color="primary">
                GT
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar50" border="extra_small" color="white">
                Wh
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar51" color="dark">
                DA
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar22" color="info">
                GT
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar23" border="extra_small" color="secondary">
                SE
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar24">
                DB
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar25" border="extra_small" color="warning">
                MD
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar26" color="danger">
                LG
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar27" color="success">
                JL
              </.avatar>
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="how-display-images">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#how-display-images"}>
              How to display images
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            By using the src prop and specifying the path to your image, you can easily display
            any desired image within the <.link navigate={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar"}>Mishka Chelekom Avatar component</.link>.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_12}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar
                id="avatar34"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar2.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar
                id="avatar35"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar3.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar
                id="avatar36"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar4.jpg"}
              />
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="how-display-icons">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#how-display-icons"}>
              How to display icons
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            By using the icon prop and selecting any Hero icon, you can display icons within the Mishka Chelekom Avatar component, providing a customizable alternative to images.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_13}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar id="avatar37">
                <:icon name="hero-users" />
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar38">
                <:icon name="hero-users" />
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar39">
                <:icon name="hero-user" />
              </.avatar>
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="how-display-text">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#how-display-text"}>
              How to display text
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The Mishka Chelekom Avatar component supports displaying user initials when no image is provided. This ensures a consistent and personalized representation for each user, offering a fallback option that maintains the visual structure of the interface.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_14}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar id="avatar40">
                TG
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar41">
                MD
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar42">
                SB
              </.avatar>
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="size-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#size-prop"}>
              Size prop in Phoenix Liveview component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The size prop in the Mishka Chelekom Avatar component allows you to control the avatar’s dimensions. You can choose from predefined sizes, such as <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>, ensuring that the avatar fits seamlessly into your design. , you can also apply your own custom class or Tailwind CSS class to add custom sizes to the avatar.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_15}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar id="avatar43" size="extra_small" color="silver">
                TG
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar
                id="avatar44"
                size="small"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar4.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar
                id="avatar45"
                size="medium"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar1.png"}
                rounded="full"
              />

              <.avatar id="avatar46" size="large">
                <:icon name="hero-users" color="dawn" />
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar47" size="extra_large">
                <:icon name="hero-star" color="misc" />
              </.avatar>
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="border-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#border-prop"}>
              Border prop in Phoenix Liveview component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The border prop in the Mishka Chelekom Avatar component allows you to control the avatar’s border size. You can choose from predefined values, such as <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, and
            <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>
            , you can also apply your own custom class or Tailwind CSS class to add custom border effects to the avatar.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_16}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar id="avatar48" size="extra_large" border="extra_small" color="primary">
                TG
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar
                id="avatar49"
                size="extra_large"
                border="small"
                color="warning"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar5.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar id="avatar" size="extra_large" border="medium" color="secondary">
                JJ
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar50" size="extra_large" border="large" color="success">
                <:icon name="hero-photo" />
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar51" size="extra_large" border="extra_large" color="danger">
                <:icon name="hero-heart" />
              </.avatar>
            </div>
          </.custom_code_wrapper>

          <.heading2 margin="my-5" id="rounded-prop">
            <.link patch={~p"/chelekom/docs/avatar/#rounded-prop"}>
              Rounded prop in Phoenix Liveview component
            </.link>
          </.heading2>

          <.cp>
            The Rounded prop in the Mishka Chelekom Avatar component allows you to control the avatar’s Rounded size. You can choose from predefined values, such as <.custom_inline_code>extra_small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>small</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>medium</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>large</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>extra_large</.custom_inline_code>, <.custom_inline_code>full</.custom_inline_code>, and <.custom_inline_code>none</.custom_inline_code>. , you can also apply your own custom class or Tailwind CSS class to add custom border radius effects to the avatar.
          </.cp>

          <.custom_code_wrapper elements_class="[&>*]:mb-2 text-sm" code={@code_17}>
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <.avatar id="avatar52" size="extra_large" rounded="extra_small">
                TG
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar
                id="avatar53"
                size="extra_large"
                rounded="small"
                color="warning"
                alt="Mishka Chelekom avatar component"
                src={~p"/images/avatar5.jpg"}
              />
              <.avatar id="avatar54" size="extra_large" rounded="medium" color="secondary">
                JJ
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar55" size="extra_large" rounded="large" color="success">
                <:icon name="hero-photo" />
              </.avatar>
              <.avatar id="avatar56" size="extra_large" rounded="extra_large" color="warning">
